## Errors & Mistakes
- The FIRST verification script used `set -e`, which aborted on `diff`'s
  exit code 1 (differences found) before printing any results. Re-ran the
  identical construction WITHOUT `set -e`; `diff` exit 1 is the EXPECTED
  outcome here (it proves the intended difference exists). No content was
  affected -- the abort was purely a display/process hiccup. Corrected by
  dropping `set -e` and treating `diff` exit 1 as success for "files
  differ as intended" checks. Lesson: do not combine `set -e` with
  commands (diff, grep) whose non-zero exit is a positive signal.
- No other errors. No force-push. No rewriting of existing commits. The
  real index and working tree were never modified.

