## Hints for Future Agents
- To commit a SINGLE file's specific change while a repo has an unmerged
  path and unrelated staged/dirty content -- WITHOUT disturbing the real
  index or working tree -- use a process-scoped
  `GIT_INDEX_FILE=/tmp/xxx` + `git read-tree HEAD` + `git hash-object -w`
  + `git update-index --cacheinfo <mode>,<sha>,<path>` + `git write-tree`
  + `git commit-tree <tree> -p HEAD -F <msg>`, then
  `git update-ref refs/heads/master <newcommit>` (fast-forward) and
  `git push`. The real .git/index and the working tree are never touched.
- The transient `model_reasoning_effort = "ultra"` lives ONLY in the
  STAGED index blob (c3139f6) of codex_config.toml; it is NOT in HEAD and
